        public void selectEntry(String label)
        Description copied from interface: Dropdownbox
        Selects an entry of this Dropdownbox by its label. If the label is null or marked as null, the operation is not executed. It the label is marked as empty, it will be replaced with "".
        Specified by:
        selectEntry in interface Dropdownbox
        Parameters:
        label - Label of the entry to select.

        Specified by:

      • assertHasLabels

        public void assertHasLabels(boolean checkOrder,
                            String... labels)
        Description copied from interface: Dropdownbox
        Checks if this Dropdownbox has the expected labels (and only these). The check fails if:
        • order of the Labels is wrong, and checkOrder is true
        • not every Label exists in the Dropdown
        • a non-listed Label exists in the Dropdown
        If only one label is passed and it is null or marked as null, the operation will not be executed.
        Specified by:
        assertHasLabels in interface Dropdownbox
        Parameters:
        checkOrder - if true, order of the labels will be checked, otherwise, the order is not important.
        labels - which should be checked
